"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-04-10-paris-2024-qualifier-ellis-disappointed-with-banyanas-failure-to-qualify-for-olympics\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  Banyana Banyana of South Africa head coach, Desiree Ellis could not hide her disappointment after the African champions failed to secure a berth at the 2024 Olympic Games.  Ellis' side were held to a 0-0 draw by the Super Falcons of Nigeria in the second leg of their fourth round tie at the Loftus Versfeld Stadium, Pretoria, on Tuesday night.  Nigeria edged the contest 1-0 on aggregate.  Banyana looked flat and struggled to break down the Super Falcons defence during the match.  Ellis could not hide her frustrations after seeing her miss out on the Olympics for the second consecutive time.  \\\"We knew that coming into this game, we needed to score. We also knew that we needed to score as early as possible because the longer the game went on, the more desperate we would become,\\\" she was quoted by The Sowetan.  \\\"We did not start well. We changed the formation slightly because we needed to score and we went with three up front. They got the chance early on and that's the only opportunity they got in the half.  \\\"But we did not go forward as much as we wanted in the first half. We made a couple of changes in the second half and threw the kitchen sink at them unfortunately, that elusive goal did not go in.  \\\"And for that, we are very disappointed. We also know the fans are disappointed, but I think we can be very proud of this team. They gave it their best shot.\\\"  Paris 2024: Super Falcons will shine at Olympics - Oparanozie  Paris 2024 qualifier: Why Super Falcons beat Banyana Banyana to Olympics ticket - Waldrum  WAFCON 2024: South Africa coach, Ellis rues missed chances in defeat to Super Falcons  WAFCON 2024: How Banyana can beat Super Falcons - Dlamini  WAFCON 2024: South Africa do not need any motivation to beat Super Falcons - Ellis  WAFCON 2024: South Africa know how to beat Super Falcons - Ellis  Olympics: Sack Sports Minister John Enoh, probe Ministry - Adeyanju writes Tinubu  Olympics: Nigerian only participated in sports that do not need investment - Seun Kuti  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"